The paper deals with path planning for an autonomous mobile robot, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed algorithm uses optimization techniques such as Particle Swarm Optimization and Modified Frequency Bat algorithm, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses obstacle detection and avoidance, which is a key aspect of control systems (cs.SY). The algorithm involves processing sensor data, which could be related to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the optimization algorithm used in the paper involves tuning parameters, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG).
